As another example of what the investigators might have selected as a stopping guideline in designing the trial, enrollment in any intervention group could be stopped if the probability of a 5 % absolute increase in mortality (the RD being less than negative 5 %) were 50 % or greater,\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
