				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$ \widehat{R} $$\end{document}R^. Additional file 3 gives the sample code for fitting this log binomial model in WinBUGS, and shows how to calculate RRs and RDs from the model parameters for both the two-factor marginal comparisons and the three intervention groups.

For all models, trace plots showed good mixing of the 3 MCMC chains and the \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
